<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1656,2043]" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1656,1682]" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Description.</emphasis>
Body length up to 
<quantity box="[564,668,1656,1683]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="382" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.20 mm</quantity>
. Ground colour pale yellowgreen in ethanol. Eye patches dark blue. Distal part of Ant. III, Ant. IV and tibiotarsi blue pigmented. Coxae and lateral part of Abd. IV with scattered pigment. Posterior part of Abd. IV and V with an irregular transverse stripes, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[1132,1264,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 60−61" captionStartId="15.[151,264,642,666]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,607]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[151,1435,181,619]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 60−61. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 60−61, habitus. Scale bars: 60−61 = 500μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795381" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795381/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Figs 60−61</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1656,2043]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">
Antenna 0.67−0.68 times body length; antennal segment ratio as I: II: III: IV = 1: 1.41−1.75: 1.18−1.83: 1.82−2.92. Apical bulb of Ant. IV bilobed (
<figureCitation box="[642,727,1800,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. III with three rods (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1265,1800,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). Distal part of Ant. II with two rods (
<figureCitation box="[412,498,1836,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
). Ant. I with three dorsal, four ventral basal smooth spiny chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1360,1836,1863]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
). Eyes 8+8, G and H smaller than others, interocular chaetae as p, s, t mes. Dorsal cephalic chaetotaxy with four antennal (An), five median (an additional mac between M2 and M3) and eight sutural (S) mac (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1198,1908,1935]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). Prelabral and labral chaetae as 4/5, 5, 4, prelabral chaetae ciliate, other smooth, four labral papillae with one minute denticle each (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). Lateral process (l.p.) of labial papilla E differentiated, as thick as normal chaeta with tip not reaching apex of papilla E (
<figureCitation box="[265,348,2016,2043]" captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
). Chaetal formula of labial base as MREL1L2, all ciliate, E rarely smooth, R/M as 0.55−0.73 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="383" pageId="11" pageNumber="382">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Subapical chaeta of maxillary outer lobe thin, subequal to apical one; three smooth hairs on sublobal plate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 62−70" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1864,1888]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,703,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-35@15.[151,1436,691,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62−70. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 62, apex of Ant. IV; 63, distal part of Ant. III; 64, distal part of Ant. II; 65, basal Ant. I; 66, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 67, labrum; 68, lateral process of labial palp; 69, labium; 70, maxillary outer lobe. Scale bars: 62−70 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795383/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
Th. II with four (m1, m2, m2i, m2i2) mac on T1 area, five (a5, m4, m4i, m4p, m5) mac on T2 area, 29−35 posterior mac, one ms and two se. Th. III with 40−43 mac and two se (
<figureCitation box="[914,998,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 71−77" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1383,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[194,1393,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 71−77. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 71, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 72, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 73, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 74, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg; 75, trochanteral organ; 76, hind foot complex; 77, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 71−77 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Pseudopores on coxa I−III as 1, 2−4, 1, respectively; coxal macrochaetal formula as 3/4+1, 3/4+2 (
<figureCitation box="[844,978,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 71−77" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1383,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[194,1393,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 71−77. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 71, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 72, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 73, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 74, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg; 75, trochanteral organ; 76, hind foot complex; 77, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 71−77 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Figs 72−74</figureCitation>
). Trochanteral organ with 49−66 smooth spiny chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[320,406,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 71−77" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1383,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[194,1393,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 71−77. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 71, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 72, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 73, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 74, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg; 75, trochanteral organ; 76, hind foot complex; 77, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 71−77 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Tenent hair thick with its tip clavate, almost equal to than inner edge of unguis in length. Unguis with four inner teeth, basal pair located 0.47−0.51 distance from base of inner edge of unguis, distal unpaired two respectively at 0.70−0.72 and 0.84−0.85 distance from base. Unguiculus lanceolate, outer edge slightly serrate (
<figureCitation box="[241,325,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 71−77" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1383,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[194,1393,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 71−77. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 71, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 72, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 73, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 74, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg; 75, trochanteral organ; 76, hind foot complex; 77, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 71−77 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">
Abd. IV 5.38−6.10 times Abd. III in dorsal axial length. Abd. I with 11 (a1, a1a, a2, a3, a5, m2−4, m2i, m4i, m4p), ms antero-external to se. Abd. II with two (a2, a3) mac on A1 area, four (m3, m3e, m3ea, m3ep) mac on A2 area, one (m5) lateral mac and two se. Abd. III with one (a2) mac on A4 area, one (m3) mac on A5 area and four (am6, pm6, m7a, p6) lateral mac, one ms and two se (
<figureCitation box="[752,836,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 71−77" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[214,1383,191,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-21@16.[194,1393,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 71−77. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 71, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 72, coxal macrochaetal formula of fore leg; 73, coxal macrochaetal formula of middle leg; 74, coxal macrochaetal formula of hind leg; 75, trochanteral organ; 76, hind foot complex; 77, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III. Scale bars: 71−77 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795385" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Abd. IV anterior with 6−9 mac arranged in irregular transverse row, posterior with 6−7 (A5−6, B5−6, Ae7, Ae5pp) central mac, lateral with 19−21 mac (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1363,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 78−80" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1216,1240]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,188,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 78−80. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 78, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 79, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 80, anterior face of ventral tube. Scale bars: 78−80 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795389/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
). Abd. V with three se (
<figureCitation box="[333,417,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 78−80" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1216,1240]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,188,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 78−80. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 78, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 79, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 80, anterior face of ventral tube. Scale bars: 78−80 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795389/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
). Anterior face of ventral tube with 35−36 ciliate chaetae, line connecting proximal (Pr) and external-distal (Ed) mac oblique to median furrow (
<figureCitation box="[737,822,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 78−80" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1216,1240]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,188,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-17@17.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 78−80. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 78, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 79, chaetotaxy of Abd. V; 80, anterior face of ventral tube. Scale bars: 78−80 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795389/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
); posterior face with four distal smooth and numerous ciliate chaetae (
<figureCitation box="[328,412,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 81−85" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,195,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1584]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 81−85. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 81, posterior face of ventral tube; 82, manubrial plaque; 83, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 84, basal dens; 85, mucro. Scale bars: 81−85 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795391/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
); lateral flap not seen wholly. Manubrial plate dorsally with 9−13 ciliate chaetae and three pseudopores (
<figureCitation box="[305,390,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 81−85" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,195,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1584]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 81−85. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 81, posterior face of ventral tube; 82, manubrial plaque; 83, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 84, basal dens; 85, mucro. Scale bars: 81−85 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795391/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
); ventrally with 38 ciliate chaetae on each side (
<figureCitation box="[917,999,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 81−85" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,195,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1584]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 81−85. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 81, posterior face of ventral tube; 82, manubrial plaque; 83, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 84, basal dens; 85, mucro. Scale bars: 81−85 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795391/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
). Dens with 58−80 smooth inner spines (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 81−85" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,195,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1584]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 81−85. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 81, posterior face of ventral tube; 82, manubrial plaque; 83, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 84, basal dens; 85, mucro. Scale bars: 81−85 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795391/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Mucro bidentate with subapical tooth larger than apical one; tip of basal spine slightly exceeding apex of subapical tooth; distal smooth of dens shorter than mucro in length (
<figureCitation box="[915,998,834,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 81−85" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1608,1632]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,195,1575]" captionTargetId="figure-21@20.[151,1436,181,1584]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 81−85. Homidia maijiensis sp. nov. 81, posterior face of ventral tube; 82, manubrial plaque; 83, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 84, basal dens; 85, mucro. Scale bars: 81−85 = 20μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6795391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6795391/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="383">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
