<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="388" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1322,1673]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1323,1349]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">Ecology.</emphasis>
Found in rotten leaf, mainly composed of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">
<taxonomicName authority=", Betula Platyphylla" authorityName="Betula Platyphylla" box="[779,1210,1322,1348]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tabuliformis">Pinus tabuliformis, Betula Platyphylla</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">Quercus variabilis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,779,1394,1421]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1322,1673]" box="[199,779,1394,1421]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1395,1421]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after its locality: Maiji District.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="388" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1322,1673]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1431,1457]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is characterised for its yellowgreen ground colour, labial base chaetae and dental spines. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lee &amp; Park, 1984" authorityName="Lee &amp; Park" authorityYear="1984" box="[395,734,1466,1493]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Homidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis box="[395,528,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">H. bilineata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, B. H. &amp; Park, K. H." box="[534,734,1466,1493]" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" pagination="177 - 188" refId="ref6457" refString="Lee, B. H. &amp; Park, K. H. (1984) Some Entomobryidae including six new species and one new record of cave form (Collembola) from Korea. Korean journal of Zoology, 27 (3), 177 - 188." type="journal article" year="1984">Lee &amp; Park, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Szeptycki, 1973" authorityName="Szeptycki" authorityYear="1973" box="[744,1125,1466,1493]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Homidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="17" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phjongjangica">
<emphasis box="[744,940,1466,1492]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="388">H. phjongjangica</emphasis>
